# CODEOWNERS - Define code ownership for review requirements
# See: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Round-20 audit fix #1: paths previously listed
# (/arc-primitives/, /arc-core/, /arc-hybrid/) were stale. The first
# and third don't exist; the second is an empty stub. All current
# crypto code lives under /latticearc/ and /latticearc-cli/, which
# previously fell through to the catch-all `*` rule and got no
# security-team review.

# Default owners for everything in the repo
* @LatticeArc/maintainers

# === Cryptographic code (requires security review) ===
# Published crate — every commit touches crypto surface.
/latticearc/ @LatticeArc/security-team
# CLI binds the public crypto API and handles secret material at rest
# (passphrases, decrypted plaintext, key files).
/latticearc-cli/ @LatticeArc/security-team
# Workspace test crate: KAT validation, FIPS compliance, side-channel,
# regression. Treat any change here as security-relevant.
/tests/ @LatticeArc/security-team

# === Security-sensitive supporting files ===
SECURITY.md @LatticeArc/security-team
/fuzz/ @LatticeArc/security-team
/clippy.toml @LatticeArc/security-team
/deny.toml @LatticeArc/security-team
/docs/MODULE_PATTERNS.md @LatticeArc/security-team
/docs/SECRET_TYPE_INVARIANTS.md @LatticeArc/security-team
/docs/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md @LatticeArc/security-team
/docs/FORMAL_VERIFICATION.md @LatticeArc/security-team

# === CI/CD workflows ===
# Lint suite + audit-time guardrails are security-sensitive: a malicious
# or careless change to lint-extras.yml could disable the regression
# blockers without that being obvious in a code review.
/.github/workflows/ @LatticeArc/maintainers
/.github/workflows/lint-extras.yml @LatticeArc/security-team
/.github/workflows/sanitizers.yml @LatticeArc/security-team
/.github/workflows/kani.yml @LatticeArc/security-team
/.github/workflows/release.yml @LatticeArc/security-team
/hooks/ @LatticeArc/security-team
